nodes.bodyText:
I just use the easy way.

IMHO, your meaning by saying "easy" is the data structure (array) itself, but in this case, we're tackling the thread-visibilities, I'd say it would be much more straightforward to use java.util.concurrent.atomic.AtomicReferenceArray than assigning the field to it self, Java programmers should be familiar with the former after all, my personal thought;
And you just brought me the interest to do a benchmark on the two solutions, in terms of the performance, check the following benchmark and results:
